BRISBANE - World champion long jumper Luvo Manyonga set a new event record as he sprung to gold at the Commonwealth Games at Australia's Gold Coast on Wednesday. GOLD FOR LUVO MANYONGA!
		
		He's won the men's long jump with a new Commonwealth Games record of 8.41 metres. Compatriot Ruswahl Samaai picked up bronze. #GC2018 pic.twitter.com/sGWTEuRU0U Manyonga produced a sixth and final jump of 8.41 metres to send to the history books the previous mark of 8.34 set by Australian Henry Frayne during the qualifying round on Tuesday. Despite the record leap, the man who grew up in Paarl in the Western Cape was always in control, in posting a fourth jump of 8.35 to ease to the front in the event. GALLERY: Commonwealth medals keep rolling in for SA Frayne took silver with 8.24 with another South African, World Championship bronze medalist Ruswahl Samaai, finishing third with 8.22. There was more good news for Team SA on the shot put scene, with Reinhardt Hamman recording a season-best throw of 13.15 to claim the bronze medal. The other South African in the competition, Juarne Jenkinson, ended eighth with a best on the night of 9.63. READ: SA commends Caster Semenya's gold rush at Commonwealth Games Gold went to Australian Carmen Crombie with an evening best of 15.74 on count-back, with countryman Marty Jackson recording the same distance but ending with silver. At the end of the seventh day's competition, Team SA's medal tally stands at 25, comprising of 10 golds, six silvers and nine bronzes. African News Agency